               <physDesc>
                  <p>(1) Thanks to Emmanuel Francis for providing us with the reference to this
                     passage and a draft translation of its content. (2) In BN-INDIEN 973β,
                     cāṟṟumīka° most probably stands for sāttvika. Interesting is the
                     hypercorrection: the occurrence of the standard Tam. ṟṟ instead of colloquial
                     tt betrays the fact that the word was considered to be of Tam. instead of Skt.
                     origin. (3) BN-INDIEN 973β has a syntactic ambiguity: the date can refer to
                     either paṭikkiṉṟa or eḻuti niṟavēriṉatu muṟṟum. We opt for the latter
                     interpretation, but the former would also be a correct interpretation. (4) Note
                     the peculiar way of writing the glyph ṟa, e.g. [100r3].</p>
               </physDesc>
