         <div type="traslation">
            <head>Translation</head>
            <p>Jovian year Cupāṉu, month of Cittirai, 31st, Monday, bright fortnight, third [lunar
               day], 29 nāḻikais in the constellation of ṟōkaṇi, 27 nāḻikais in the yōkam called
               Atikaṇṭam, 14 3/16 nāḻikais in the karaṇam of Pālavā, 2 ½ nāḻikais in the karaṇam
               (°karaṇam) of Kaulavā, 27 3/16 nāḻikais in the day (tivi), 8 ¼ nāḻikais in the night
               (ṟāttiri), tiyācciyam on the 8 3/16 nāḻikais at night (ṟā) – in this auspicious day
               with an auspicious conjunction [of calendrical elements]; at dawn (utittu), 22 ¾
               nāḻikais at night (ṟā) – in the Kaṉṉiyā lakkaṇam; in the Cāṟṟumīkam vēḷai at night;
               the Nālaṭiyār, which was recited (paṭikkiṉṟa) by Cirañcīvi Vīṟacāmi son of
               Ṟaṅkayanāyakkar, was fully copied and completed. It is desirable to have a long life
               (tīṟkāyicu, read tīrkkāyucu). The teacher (upāttiyār) Aṇṇāmalai copied it</p>
         </div>
